    "Body": "Research and Editorial Intern at The Block Working at The Block is one of the most enjoyable, fulfilling, and challenging experiences you\u2019ll have in your career. The Block is the leading research, analysis and news brand in the digital asset space. Founded in 2018 and based in NYC, The Block\u2019s team is spread across 7 times zones, covering the global cryptocurrency and blockchain space 24/7. Through The Block\u2019s website + newsletter, the Genesis research brand, our podcast \u201cThe Scoop,\u201d hosted + 3rd party events and community participation, we interact daily with tens of thousands of crypto natives, financial market participants, Fortune 500 professionals, global service providers, government leaders and more. The Block delivers deep insight into how this emerging sector interacts with traditional finance, technology, governments and markets. The Block\u2019s foundation is simple: we are the first and final word in digital assets. Job Description Company Intro Working at The Block is one of the most enjoyable, fulfilling, and challenging experiences you\u2019ll have in your career. We are on the frontier of one of the most thrilling ecosystems in technology and money: cryptocurrency and blockchain. We provide a \u201cCrypto Simplified\u201d experience for experts and enthusiasts alike by introducing a trusted, accessible brand, and set of products into a thicket of dense, high noise, and often fraudulent sources of information. The Block\u2019s value proposition is built around credible and real-time insight, analysis, news, and information about this fast-moving, complex, and critically important space. Role Intro As a Research and Editorial Intern at The Block, you will join our team and support our product, community, and business. One day you will write a detailed explainer on zero-knowledge proofs. Another day, you will help choose which stories we track and how we write about them. The Block is a unique company in that it involves multiple exciting lines of business, each with its own technical opportunities and hard problems to solve. The business lines include: media and information at www.theblockcrypto.com, the cryptocurrency and blockchain community platform we are building, and a subscription media product that will involve payment systems and processing. This breadth of responsibility should be thrilling to an aspiring reporter -- those who can challenge themselves across multiple areas. In addition to your editorial experience, you will be a critical member of the editorial team. You will work hand-in-hand with our Director of Research, and Director of News to ensure that we are delivering comprehensive reporting to our readers. You will communicate with the editorial team as well as the entire company in order to ensure we are delivering the best products and experiences to the market. Your ability to synthesize and convey your ideas publicly will be important, as The Block is a high profile organization that receives numerous requests for public appearances, knowledge sharing, and community interaction. In summary, this is an early stage opportunity that combines aspects of both a technology and media company that together, create a unique company! As a Research and Editorial Intern, you will\u2026 Contribute to the editorial elements of The Block\u2019s strategy and ensure it aligns with the company\u2019s business goals Explore topics of interest and create pieces of research and analysis to bring new insights to the community Synthesize and relay relevant news in an approachable way to a broad reader base Ensure that The Block\u2019s news feed provides a complete set of stories to keep our readers informed and intelligent We look for teammates who have\u2026. Experience as a blogger, writer, or reporter Good instincts for what readers find interesting A passion for cryptocurrencies and blockchain technology The ability to communicate complicated ideas concisely A \u201ccan do\u201d attitude and strong strategic problem solver An appreciation of elementary level statistics A desire to educate and improve the wider community Who will you work with? Mike Dudas, Co-founder and CEO Jake McGraw, Co-founder and CTO Mike McCaffrey, Chief of Staff, Director of Operations Steven Zheng, Head of Research Larry Cermak, Director of Research Frank Chaparro, Director of News, Senior Correspondent Isabel Woodford, Reporter Our team values and celebrates our diverse backgrounds. Being open about who we are and what we do allows us to do the best work of our lives. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. Apply for this job ???????????????????????? New York, NY ", 
